This is based on the Bridle sample :ref:`button-sample` in polling mode.

.. zephyr-app-commands::
   :app: bridle/samples/button
   :build-dir: tcs_604_ard
   :board: nucleo_f746zg
   :shield: "tcs_604_ard grove_btn_d4 grove_led_d3 grove_sens_bmp280 tcs_604_x_grove_testbed"
   :conf: prj-poll.conf
   :west-args: -p
   :goals: flash
   :host-os: unix
   :compact:

.. rubric:: Sample Output

After flashing, the extra connected |LED Shields| by :rpi-pico-pio:`IO3`
at :hwftlbl-con:`D3` starts to light up in time with the key press on the
extra connected |Button Shields| by :rpi-pico-pio:`IO4` at :hwftlbl-con:`D4`
(see wiring above).

You should see the following message on the console:

   .. container:: highlight highlight-console notranslate

      .. parsed-literal::

         \*\*\* Booting Zephyr OS build |zephyr_version_em|\ *â€¦*\*\*\*
         Set up button at sc18is604-0-gpio pin 4
         Set up LED at sc18is604-0-gpio pin 3
         Press the button
